<article>

      <header class="row">
      <div class="columns">
        <h2 class="sub-page-title contrast">Construction and repair permits</h2>      </div>
    </header>
  

  <div data-swiftype-index='true' class="entry-content">

    
    
      



    

          <!-- WYSIWYG content -->
      <section class="wysiwyg-content">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="small-24 columns">
            <div class="row"><div class="columns"><div class="panel info info-block mbl"><p><p> The primary focus of the Department of Licenses and Inspections (L&amp;I) is public safety. Permits allow L&amp;I to perform reviews and conduct inspections of construction and related activities taking place in Philadelphia. </p>
</p></div></div></div>
<p>Jump to:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#building-and-safety-codes">Building and safety codes</a></li>
<li><a href="#preliminary-plan-review">Preliminary plan review</a></li>
<li><a href="#permits-for-construction-and-repair">Permits for construction and repair</a></li>
<li><a href="#for-repairs-to-dangerous-buildings">Repairs to dangerous buildings</a></li>
<li><a href="#permit-documents">Permit documents</a></li>
<li><a href="#permit-navigator-pilot">Permit Navigator Pilot</a></li>
</ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- End WYSIWYG content -->
    
  
<!-- Collection page -->
  <section class="mtl">

    <div class="one-quarter-layout">

    
    
                  
              <!-- Free text -->
                            
          <div class="row one-quarter-row mvl">
            <div class="columns medium-6">
                <h3 id="building-and-safety-codes">Building and safety codes </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="columns medium-18">
                          <p>The permit process helps to ensure that projects comply with <a href="https://www.phila.gov/departments/department-of-licenses-and-inspections/resources/applicable-codes/">applicable codes</a>.</p>
<p>Building permits allow work or a change in activity to be done at a building or on a lot. You must file permit applications and pay related fees in order to be issued a permit.</p>
                          </div>

          </div>
                    <!-- Free text -->
      
      
      
      
      
      
                          <hr class="margin-auto"/>
      
    
                  
              <!-- Free text -->
                            
          <div class="row one-quarter-row mvl">
            <div class="columns medium-6">
                <h3 id="preliminary-plan-review">Preliminary plan review</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="columns medium-18">
                          <p>You have the option of having an L&amp;I staff member to review plans and have them answer and/or prepare documentation to address your concerns. To do this, you should <a href="https://www.phila.gov/services/permits-violations-licenses/get-construction-approval-and-review/request-a-preliminary-review-of-construction-projects/">request a preliminary plan review.</a></p>
<p>Once you are ready to build, you&#8217;ll need to apply for individual permits.</p>
                          </div>

          </div>
                    <!-- Free text -->
      
      
      
      
      
      
                          <hr class="margin-auto"/>
      
    
                      <div class="row one-quarter-row mvl collection-services">
          <div class="columns medium-6">
            <h3 id="permits-for-construction-and-repair">Permits for construction and repair</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="columns medium-18">
            <div class="row grid-x fat-gutter">
                          <div class="flex-container auto small-24 medium-8 column end">
                <a href="https://www.phila.gov/services/permits-violations-licenses/apply-for-a-permit/building-and-repair-permits/get-permits-without-plans-ez-permits/" class="card sub-topic">
                  <div class="content-block">
                    <h4 class="h3">Get permits without plans (EZ permits)</h3>
                    Get a permit for construction or renovation without submitting plans.                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>
                          <div class="flex-container auto small-24 medium-8 column end">
                <a href="https://www.phila.gov/services/permits-violations-licenses/apply-for-a-permit/building-and-repair-permits/" class="card sub-topic">
                  <div class="content-block">
                    <h4 class="h3">Building and repair permits</h3>
                    How to get permits and approvals to do building and repair.                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>
                        </div>
          </div>
        </div>
                  
      
      
      
      
      
      
                          <hr class="margin-auto"/>
      
    
                      <div class="row one-quarter-row mvl collection-services">
          <div class="columns medium-6">
            <h3 id="for-repairs-to-dangerous-buildings">For repairs to dangerous buildings</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="columns medium-18">
            <div class="row grid-x fat-gutter">
                          <div class="flex-container auto small-24 medium-8 column end">
                <a href="https://www.phila.gov/services/permits-violations-licenses/apply-for-a-permit/building-and-repair-permits/get-a-make-safe-permit-for-a-dangerous-building/" class="card sub-topic">
                  <div class="content-block">
                    <h4 class="h3">Get a Make Safe Permit for a dangerous building</h3>
                    How to get a permit to fix a structure marked as unsafe or imminently dangerous.                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>
                        </div>
          </div>
        </div>
                  
      
      
      
      
      
      
                          <hr class="margin-auto"/>
      
    
                  
      
      
              <!-- Resource group wrapper -->
<div class="row one-quarter-row mvl">
  <div class="columns medium-6">
                      <h3 id="permit-documents">Permit documents</h3>
        </div>
  <div class="columns medium-18 pbxl">
          <div class="mbl">
        <p>These documents will help guide you through your building or repair project. You can also refer to <a href="https://www.phila.gov/departments/department-of-licenses-and-inspections/code-bulletins/">code bulletins</a> to learn more.</p>
      </div>
                    <div class="mbl">
                                      
<section class="mtl">
    
                    <div class="grid-container">
            <div class="grid-x grid-padding-x one-quarter-row  mvm">
